1
00:00:11,667 --> 00:00:12,767
Why are you doing this to me?

2
00:00:12,833 --> 00:00:14,600
Is it because I became
close to your daughter?

3
00:00:14,667 --> 00:00:16,600
You did this to yourself, Emma.

4
00:00:16,667 --> 00:00:19,000
- Go get that woman.
- Why are they arresting Emma?

5
00:00:19,067 --> 00:00:20,433
You planted all that!

6
00:00:20,500 --> 00:00:22,333
Even the necklace in the room!

7
00:00:22,400 --> 00:00:26,400
Sometimes, I wish Emma
was my mother.

8
00:00:26,467 --> 00:00:28,467
I was accused of theft.

9
00:00:28,533 --> 00:00:29,600
That's wrong.

10
00:00:29,667 --> 00:00:30,667
Are you going to extort
money from me again?

11
00:00:30,733 --> 00:00:32,467
My daughter is innocent.

12
00:00:32,533 --> 00:00:33,900
So, I'm begging you.

13
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:35,433
Please drop the case.

14
00:00:35,500 --> 00:00:37,400
And why would I do that?

15
00:00:37,467 --> 00:00:39,900
Let's go to a radio station.

16
00:00:39,967 --> 00:00:43,200
Mom, I don't want to ruin
the kid's name and dignity.

17
00:00:43,267 --> 00:00:48,733
I just wonder how my necklace
ended up in the dark room.

18
00:00:48,800 --> 00:00:51,733
I know Emma isn't
that kind of person.

19
00:00:51,800 --> 00:00:54,200
Unless she was framed up.

20
00:01:30,667 --> 00:01:33,033
Emma's poisoning your brain!

21
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:36,933
You're growing horns too!

22
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:38,967
Are you taking Emma's side?

23
00:01:39,033 --> 00:01:39,767
Mommy, no!
No, Mommy!

24
00:01:40,600 --> 00:01:41,567
No, no!

25
00:01:41,633 --> 00:01:42,567
No, Mommy!

26
00:01:42,633 --> 00:01:43,800
- No, Mommy!
- Are you really like that?

27
00:01:43,867 --> 00:01:45,600
- You're ungrateful!
- Mommy, no!

28
00:01:46,133 --> 00:01:47,800
Mommy, no!

29
00:01:48,100 --> 00:01:49,467
- No, Mommy!
- Ma'am!

30
00:01:49,533 --> 00:01:50,833
Ma'am, please stop!

31
00:01:50,900 --> 00:01:52,067
Ma'am! Have mercy on her!

32
00:01:52,133 --> 00:01:53,000
Ma'am, please stop!

33
00:01:53,067 --> 00:01:54,800
Ma'am!

34
00:01:54,867 --> 00:01:56,800
Ma'am, please stop!

35
00:01:58,567 --> 00:02:01,300
Did you hear how she
talked back to me?

36
00:02:03,467 --> 00:02:05,667
You ungrateful child!

37
00:02:07,167 --> 00:02:08,933
Unappreciative!

38
00:02:09,733 --> 00:02:12,000
I sacrificed
everything for you!

39
00:02:12,867 --> 00:02:16,633
I gave up the best years
of my life to raise you, Mookie!

40
00:02:17,933 --> 00:02:19,800
I gave you everything!

41
00:02:23,867 --> 00:02:26,233
Don't try my patience.

42
00:02:27,567 --> 00:02:32,733
Because you don't know
what else I can do to you.

43
00:02:34,367 --> 00:02:35,033
Ma'am.

44
00:02:35,100 --> 00:02:36,233
Please, stop.

45
00:02:38,067 --> 00:02:39,833
Mookie, are you okay?

46
00:02:39,900 --> 00:02:40,600
I'm sorry.

47
00:02:55,233 --> 00:02:58,367
They are Elsa and Eva.

48
00:03:01,033 --> 00:03:04,933
Mom, you never mentioned
anything about them before.

49
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:06,967
I didn't mention them because...

50
00:03:09,100 --> 00:03:10,467
I feel like...

51
00:03:11,833 --> 00:03:13,667
I'm a bad mother.

52
00:03:17,900 --> 00:03:19,700
I'm a worthless woman, Emma.

53
00:03:20,500 --> 00:03:23,533
Mom, that's not true.

54
00:03:24,300 --> 00:03:25,467
That's not true.

55
00:03:27,100 --> 00:03:28,667
You're not perfect,

56
00:03:29,567 --> 00:03:33,167
but you raised
and nurtured me well.

57
00:03:33,233 --> 00:03:37,067
And I don't judge you
on what you did.

58
00:03:37,133 --> 00:03:39,967
I know you have a reason
why you did that.

59
00:03:40,033 --> 00:03:42,033
I understand.

60
00:04:17,733 --> 00:04:22,167
I won't always be there
to help you.

61
00:04:23,500 --> 00:04:28,633
I know it's not easy,
but you have to be brave.

62
00:04:31,667 --> 00:04:36,733
Mommy said I have inner
strength and resolve.

63
00:04:37,967 --> 00:04:40,500
I need to be brave.

64
00:04:40,567 --> 00:04:42,433
I need to be strong.

65
00:04:42,500 --> 00:04:44,733
I need to pick myself up.

66
00:07:09,933 --> 00:07:10,567
Hello?

67
00:07:15,100 --> 00:07:16,300
So, you're still alive.

68
00:07:17,400 --> 00:07:18,767
What made you call?

69
00:07:53,400 --> 00:07:55,367
I told you to stop calling me.

70
00:07:56,300 --> 00:07:56,933
What?

71
00:07:57,767 --> 00:07:59,867
And why would you
come home, Jade?

72
00:08:12,300 --> 00:08:13,100
Mom.

73
00:08:13,767 --> 00:08:15,567
Can you go home?

74
00:08:15,633 --> 00:08:18,567
Please get me some clothes
so I can change.

75
00:08:20,267 --> 00:08:20,800
Okay.

76
00:08:22,733 --> 00:08:24,967
That coffee might keep
you awake all night.

77
00:08:26,900 --> 00:08:32,433
I can't stop thinking,
no matter how I close my eyes.

78
00:08:34,200 --> 00:08:35,367
Thinking?

79
00:08:36,000 --> 00:08:36,967
Of who?

80
00:08:37,733 --> 00:08:40,333
Are you thinking
about Mookie again?

81
00:08:41,167 --> 00:08:43,167
I told you so many times

82
00:08:43,233 --> 00:08:45,433
that you have no reason
to return here.

83
00:08:46,167 --> 00:08:48,433
Stay there in Japan, Jade.

84
00:08:48,500 --> 00:08:51,200
You no longer have
any business here.

85
00:08:51,933 --> 00:08:57,100
And for the last time,
stop calling me.

86
00:09:10,300 --> 00:09:11,133
What's that?

87
00:09:13,600 --> 00:09:14,367
A mouse?

88
00:09:16,133 --> 00:09:17,333
Is there a mouse here?

89
00:09:30,000 --> 00:09:30,567
Mooks.

90
00:09:35,800 --> 00:09:37,067
Are you okay, Mooks?

91
00:09:37,133 --> 00:09:38,133
You look pale.

92
00:09:39,033 --> 00:09:41,100
I'm just shocked, Zayn,
but I can manage.

93
00:09:41,167 --> 00:09:43,933
I will get up and walk
for Mommy Emma.

94
00:10:08,333 --> 00:10:09,533
Probably nothing.

95
00:10:16,767 --> 00:10:22,533
Like a deck of cards,
you're so easy to read.

96
00:10:23,433 --> 00:10:28,467
Ever since your child died,
that look in your eyes...

97
00:10:28,533 --> 00:10:29,833
that kind of look...

98
00:10:31,667 --> 00:10:34,433
it's like you're always
searching

99
00:10:34,500 --> 00:10:35,733
for something that you've lost.

100
00:10:37,867 --> 00:10:39,133
You've always had that look.

101
00:10:40,400 --> 00:10:41,700
It's always there.

102
00:10:43,867 --> 00:10:47,833
If Kayla were alive, she would
be the same age as Mookie.

103
00:10:48,833 --> 00:10:50,300
You know what, Mom?

104
00:10:50,367 --> 00:10:52,600
Every time I take care
of Mookie,

105
00:10:53,733 --> 00:10:55,633
I feel like I'm the one healing.

106
00:10:57,533 --> 00:11:00,500
She healed the wound that I had
been carrying for a long time.

107
00:11:02,667 --> 00:11:03,667
You're lucky.

108
00:11:05,600 --> 00:11:07,300
In the game cards,

109
00:11:07,400 --> 00:11:09,333
you were given the card
that you needed.

110
00:11:10,433 --> 00:11:15,433
I feel better whenever
I'm with Mookie.

111
00:11:16,833 --> 00:11:20,700
I wish I could see her now.

112
00:11:27,433 --> 00:11:29,567
I asked my dad for help.

113
00:11:29,633 --> 00:11:32,200
He talked to the general
that he knows.

114
00:11:32,267 --> 00:11:34,133
He said we could go
to the police station.

115
00:11:38,133 --> 00:11:39,367
Are you okay, Mookie?

116
00:11:41,267 --> 00:11:44,500
You can tell me if
something's bothering you.

117
00:11:46,433 --> 00:11:51,467
I hope my mom won't
go into my room.

118
00:11:51,533 --> 00:11:55,400
No offense, but maybe she
won't expect you

119
00:11:55,467 --> 00:11:58,267
to get up and walk alone.

120
00:11:58,333 --> 00:12:02,833
I struggled so hard earlier.

121
00:12:02,900 --> 00:12:06,000
I crawled and fell.

122
00:12:09,133 --> 00:12:12,767
But while doing
all those things,

123
00:12:12,833 --> 00:12:16,600
I keep hearing Mommy Emma's
voice in my head.

124
00:12:17,833 --> 00:12:21,400
And I won't give up

125
00:12:21,467 --> 00:12:23,700
no matter how hard
and painful everything is.

126
00:12:23,767 --> 00:12:26,833
I can do it because I'm brave.

127
00:12:32,433 --> 00:12:38,100
Sorry, it's not my intention to
air out my grievances to you.

128
00:12:38,167 --> 00:12:38,733
I'm sorry.

129
00:12:38,800 --> 00:12:40,600
No, no. It's okay.

130
00:12:40,667 --> 00:12:42,467
I'm your safe space, Mookie.

131
00:12:43,367 --> 00:12:44,967
I'm here for you.

132
00:13:12,400 --> 00:13:13,000
Mom!

133
00:13:21,400 --> 00:13:22,200
Mookie!

134
00:13:24,467 --> 00:13:25,067
Mom!

135
00:13:28,200 --> 00:13:29,000
Mookie!

136
00:13:38,300 --> 00:13:41,500
Dear, you can walk
on your own now.

137
00:13:47,500 --> 00:13:48,500
Yes, Mom.

138
00:13:49,633 --> 00:13:51,300
Because you're right.

139
00:13:52,767 --> 00:13:55,800
I just really need
to try and believe.

140
00:13:56,867 --> 00:13:58,433
I can do it too.

141
00:14:02,167 --> 00:14:03,633
I believe in you.

142
00:14:05,933 --> 00:14:07,733
You're my inspiration, Mom.

143
00:14:09,733 --> 00:14:12,233
You're the miracle worker
in my life.

144
00:14:13,700 --> 00:14:15,600
My best medicine.

145
00:14:17,333 --> 00:14:19,433
You are the miracle in my life.

146
00:14:20,333 --> 00:14:21,867
You are the light...

147
00:14:22,667 --> 00:14:25,067
in my mind and heart

148
00:14:27,400 --> 00:14:30,833
whenever I'm sad
and feel hopeless.

149
00:14:39,100 --> 00:14:41,667
I'm here for you, Mom.

150
00:14:59,633 --> 00:15:02,367
I'm so happy that you
and Zayn are here.

151
00:15:03,133 --> 00:15:05,133
I just wish I could hug you.

152
00:15:05,200 --> 00:15:07,967
I could hug you tightly.

153
00:15:09,733 --> 00:15:11,000
I'm sorry, Mom.

154
00:15:12,900 --> 00:15:15,967
You shouldn't be here.

155
00:15:19,033 --> 00:15:24,167
I'm apologizing for
what mommy did to you.

156
00:15:24,233 --> 00:15:25,200
I'm really sorry, Mom.

157
00:15:25,267 --> 00:15:26,900
Sorry, sorry.

158
00:15:26,967 --> 00:15:31,067
No. You didn't do anything
wrong, dear.

159
00:15:34,400 --> 00:15:36,167
What are you doing here?

160
00:15:37,100 --> 00:15:38,167
Did you escape from home?

161
00:15:40,633 --> 00:15:44,233
I need to fix this mess, Mom.

162
00:15:45,067 --> 00:15:50,233
I want to tell the police that
you didn't steal my necklace.

163
00:15:51,000 --> 00:15:54,633
Dear, I didn't like that
you sneaked out

164
00:15:54,700 --> 00:15:56,000
even though I wanted to see you.

165
00:15:56,067 --> 00:15:57,633
I don't like what you did.

166
00:15:58,600 --> 00:16:01,433
I know you have good intentions,

167
00:16:01,500 --> 00:16:02,133
but...

168
00:16:03,133 --> 00:16:07,367
go home before your mom
finds out you left.

169
00:16:07,433 --> 00:16:08,700
Go on.

170
00:16:08,800 --> 00:16:09,767
Mom.

171
00:16:11,367 --> 00:16:14,200
I don't regret coming here.

172
00:16:15,133 --> 00:16:17,167
Because you matter to me.

173
00:16:18,733 --> 00:16:23,467
Don't give your mom
a reason to hurt you.

174
00:16:27,433 --> 00:16:28,300
Why?

175
00:16:28,367 --> 00:16:29,467
What happened?

176
00:16:29,533 --> 00:16:30,933
It's nothing, Mom.

177
00:16:31,000 --> 00:16:32,133
Mookie.

178
00:16:32,200 --> 00:16:34,033
It's nothing, Mom. I promise.

179
00:16:35,933 --> 00:16:36,700
A bruise?

180
00:16:37,900 --> 00:16:39,833
Why do you have a bruise?

181
00:16:39,900 --> 00:16:41,000
Where did you get that?

182
00:17:07,900 --> 00:17:08,567
Mookie?

183
00:17:12,100 --> 00:17:12,833
Mookie?

184
00:17:18,933 --> 00:17:19,767
Mookie!

185
00:17:24,367 --> 00:17:25,200
Mookie!

186
00:17:27,400 --> 00:17:28,000
What happened?

187
00:17:28,067 --> 00:17:29,467
Why do you have a bruise?

188
00:17:30,933 --> 00:17:32,333
It's nothing, Mom.

189
00:17:32,400 --> 00:17:35,033
I just bumped into the door.

190
00:17:35,800 --> 00:17:37,433
Don't worry about it.

191
00:17:38,733 --> 00:17:40,967
Dear, don't be afraid to talk.

192
00:17:41,033 --> 00:17:43,067
Tell the authorities.
The police are here.

193
00:17:43,133 --> 00:17:44,667
Speak up.

194
00:17:45,633 --> 00:17:47,367
Did your mom hurt you?

195
00:17:56,500 --> 00:17:58,567
I'm sorry, Mom.

196
00:17:59,533 --> 00:18:01,567
I need to go home.

197
00:18:02,867 --> 00:18:06,233
No matter the reason, she
has no right to hurt you.

198
00:18:16,467 --> 00:18:18,533
Always remember, okay?

199
00:18:18,600 --> 00:18:20,467
I'm here.

200
00:18:20,533 --> 00:18:21,633
I'll help you.

201
00:18:23,200 --> 00:18:23,867
Sorry, Mom.

202
00:18:23,933 --> 00:18:26,833
We really need to go home.

203
00:18:28,833 --> 00:18:31,167
Zayn, thank you for coming here.

204
00:18:31,233 --> 00:18:33,500
Please take care of Mookie.

205
00:18:33,567 --> 00:18:35,600
Make sure she's safe.

206
00:18:35,667 --> 00:18:37,600
Don't worry, Miss Emma.

207
00:18:37,667 --> 00:18:39,167
I'll take care of Mookie.

208
00:18:40,600 --> 00:18:42,567
Mookie, let's go.

209
00:18:51,300 --> 00:18:52,533
Mommy Emma...

210
00:18:54,233 --> 00:18:57,467
I will always pray for
and think of you.

211
00:18:59,700 --> 00:19:00,500
Me too.

212
00:19:02,067 --> 00:19:03,500
Be safe.

213
00:19:05,533 --> 00:19:06,767
Be safe.

214
00:19:10,700 --> 00:19:12,233
Sorry, Mom.

215
00:19:19,667 --> 00:19:20,700
Come on, Mookie.

216
00:20:01,500 --> 00:20:02,133
Flor?

217
00:20:04,067 --> 00:20:04,733
Flor!

218
00:20:07,167 --> 00:20:07,933
Flor!

219
00:20:08,600 --> 00:20:09,467
Flor!

220
00:20:12,333 --> 00:20:13,767
Flor, come on!

221
00:20:13,833 --> 00:20:14,867
I'm coming, Ma'am!

222
00:20:14,933 --> 00:20:15,533
I'm coming!
What's going on, Ma'am?

223
00:20:16,367 --> 00:20:17,700
Why are you calling me?

224
00:20:17,767 --> 00:20:19,633
Mookie's missing, Flor!

225
00:20:19,700 --> 00:20:20,367
What?

226
00:20:20,433 --> 00:20:21,633
Mookie's in her room, Ma'am.

227
00:20:21,700 --> 00:20:23,033
- How...
- Are you stupid?

228
00:20:23,100 --> 00:20:24,267
She's not there!

229
00:20:24,900 --> 00:20:25,767
Call the guard!
Hurry!

230
00:20:26,300 --> 00:20:27,600
Okay, okay.

231
00:20:29,133 --> 00:20:30,100
Number...

232
00:20:32,067 --> 00:20:33,333
Where did that kid go?

233
00:20:33,400 --> 00:20:34,367
He's not picking up.

234
00:20:39,033 --> 00:20:41,867
Ma'am, what if Mookie
has been kidnapped?

235
00:20:42,667 --> 00:20:43,400
Here it is.
He already answered.
Hello, guard!

236
00:20:44,300 --> 00:20:45,800
Yes. This is from
1 Hillview Lane.

237
00:20:45,867 --> 00:20:47,167
Yes. Please help us.

238
00:20:47,233 --> 00:20:48,200
My employer's daughter
is missing.

239
00:20:48,267 --> 00:20:49,933
Please send a guard here.
Hurry!

240
00:20:50,000 --> 00:20:51,267
Please hurry up! Yes!

241
00:20:51,333 --> 00:20:51,833
Yes, yes.

242
00:20:51,933 --> 00:20:53,833
Okay. Thank you.

243
00:20:53,900 --> 00:20:55,767
Ma'am, the guards are
on their way here.

244
00:20:55,833 --> 00:20:57,233
If Mookie left...

245
00:20:58,033 --> 00:20:58,967
How?

246
00:20:59,567 --> 00:21:00,833
I don't know, Ma'am.

247
00:21:00,900 --> 00:21:02,967
I was already sleeping
in my room, Ma'am.

248
00:21:03,767 --> 00:21:05,200
Did she go to Emma?

249
00:21:08,133 --> 00:21:09,900
Get my cell phone and car keys.

250
00:21:10,000 --> 00:21:10,900
Hurry! It's in my room!

251
00:21:10,967 --> 00:21:12,167
- Move!
- Yes, I will.

252
00:21:20,500 --> 00:21:21,900
Darn you, Emma.

253
00:21:23,333 --> 00:21:26,367
You can't take my daughter
away from me.

254
00:21:31,300 --> 00:21:32,533
You've been quiet.

255
00:21:38,800 --> 00:21:40,500
Can I ask you something?

256
00:21:40,567 --> 00:21:41,333
What is it?

257
00:21:43,800 --> 00:21:46,467
Tell me if I'm overstepping
boundaries.

258
00:21:47,200 --> 00:21:51,000
But did you really get
that bruise from the door?

259
00:21:54,100 --> 00:21:55,867
You don't need to say anything.

260
00:21:55,933 --> 00:21:56,967
I get you.

261
00:21:58,567 --> 00:22:00,800
Miss Emma is right, you know?

262
00:22:00,867 --> 00:22:02,567
Some people can help you.

263
00:22:03,833 --> 00:22:06,300
Tell me if you need help.

264
00:22:12,567 --> 00:22:13,167
But...

265
00:22:14,333 --> 00:22:17,100
How do I tell other people
about my mother?

266
00:22:20,200 --> 00:22:21,433
It's difficult.

267
00:22:23,200 --> 00:22:24,133
It's painful.

268
00:22:26,067 --> 00:22:28,500
It's painful to think
that she's hurting me.

269
00:22:30,700 --> 00:22:31,533
Something...

270
00:22:32,700 --> 00:22:36,433
I couldn't admit
to myself for a long time.

271
00:22:37,833 --> 00:22:40,767
I make excuses whenever
she hits me.

272
00:22:42,000 --> 00:22:43,333
Sometimes, I think....

273
00:22:44,900 --> 00:22:49,500
maybe she's just
not in the mood.

274
00:22:54,267 --> 00:22:58,433
Or maybe she's also having
a hard time understanding me

275
00:22:58,500 --> 00:23:00,167
because I'm stubborn.

276
00:23:02,867 --> 00:23:04,867
Or maybe she's getting
tired of me.

277
00:23:10,967 --> 00:23:15,033
Or it's my fault why
she's hurting me.

278
00:23:16,533 --> 00:23:19,800
Sometimes, my parents
get mad at me too

279
00:23:19,867 --> 00:23:23,033
but they never laid
their hands on me.

280
00:23:26,367 --> 00:23:29,567
You could've told
Miss Emma the truth.

281
00:23:30,467 --> 00:23:31,933
You could've told
the police about it.

282
00:23:34,100 --> 00:23:34,767
But...

283
00:23:37,400 --> 00:23:38,800
But it feels like...

284
00:23:40,167 --> 00:23:41,933
I'm betraying my mom.

285
00:23:45,767 --> 00:23:47,900
I legit hope she doesn't
hurt you again.

286
00:23:48,900 --> 00:23:53,067
If your mom hurts you again,
don't be afraid to report her.

287
00:24:24,400 --> 00:24:25,400
Careful, Mookie.

288
00:24:26,733 --> 00:24:27,367
Can you do it?

289
00:24:28,800 --> 00:24:29,633
Mookie!

290
00:24:30,133 --> 00:24:31,433
Come here, you little brat!

291
00:24:31,500 --> 00:24:32,733
Where did you go?

292
00:24:32,800 --> 00:24:33,633
Come here!

293
00:24:34,500 --> 00:24:35,233
You?

294
00:24:35,300 --> 00:24:36,400
You again!

295
00:24:37,233 --> 00:24:39,367
Do you know I can sue you?

296
00:24:40,600 --> 00:24:42,567
Mommy, he's not doing
anything wrong.

297
00:24:42,633 --> 00:24:45,133
I was the one
who asked him a favor.

298
00:24:45,200 --> 00:24:49,767
If this person had brains,
he wouldn't help you escape!

299
00:24:50,867 --> 00:24:51,933
How are you, Mookie?

300
00:24:52,000 --> 00:24:53,567
Are you okay, dear?

301
00:24:53,633 --> 00:24:55,300
Where's your wheelchair?

302
00:24:56,433 --> 00:24:59,733
Mommy, I can walk now.

303
00:25:01,300 --> 00:25:02,733
You can walk?

304
00:25:02,833 --> 00:25:03,700
Since when?

305
00:25:05,300 --> 00:25:06,867
Flor, help Mookie.

306
00:25:06,933 --> 00:25:08,833
Don't force yourself!

307
00:25:08,900 --> 00:25:10,033
And, you...

308
00:25:10,100 --> 00:25:12,033
Why are you still
standing there?

309
00:25:12,100 --> 00:25:13,233
Leave!

310
00:25:14,500 --> 00:25:17,100
And you stay away
from my daughter!

311
00:25:17,167 --> 00:25:17,900
Leave!

312
00:25:17,967 --> 00:25:19,600
- Ma'am, we safely...
- Leave!

313
00:25:20,933 --> 00:25:22,233
I'll call the cops!

314
00:25:42,133 --> 00:25:43,733
Mommy, I don't want that.

315
00:25:43,800 --> 00:25:45,167
It hurts, Mommy.

316
00:25:45,233 --> 00:25:48,233
- We need to do this.
- Mommy! I said I don't want it!

317
00:25:50,200 --> 00:25:51,067
Really, Dan?

318
00:25:51,133 --> 00:25:52,567
You reported her to the
barangay?

319
00:25:52,633 --> 00:25:53,467
Yes, Emma.

320
00:25:53,533 --> 00:25:55,733
You know I can't ignore you.

321
00:25:55,800 --> 00:25:58,633
We received a complaint
against you.

322
00:25:58,700 --> 00:25:59,500
About what?

323
00:25:59,567 --> 00:26:01,833
About possible child abuse.

324
00:26:01,900 --> 00:26:03,633
Be careful with your answers.

325
00:26:03,700 --> 00:26:06,800
May we know how you got
your bruise?

326
00:26:08,100 --> 00:26:10,167
Do you think she'll talk?

327
00:26:10,267 --> 00:26:11,033
Will she confess?

328
00:26:11,900 --> 00:26:15,533
Is there something
you want to tell us, dear?
